A vintage 1960s advertising illustration style image depicting a frustrated person sitting at a mid-century modern desk, holding a small electronic security token device that's visibly malfunctioning with tiny clock gears spilling out of it. The scene shows scattered coins falling through cracks in the desk while large golden bars drift away through an open window. The color palette features muted teals, warm oranges, and cream tones typical of retro bank advertisements. The person's expression conveys exasperation, their other hand pressed against their forehead. In the background, a rotary telephone sits untouched, suggesting helplessness. The overall composition evokes the irony of penny-pinching decisions leading to significant losses, rendered in that distinctive mid-century commercial art style with visible brushwork and halftone texture effects.
